Pros:. When it works, it works well. Great audio and picture. The Wireless adapter, while a bit on the expensive side, works very well.. 
Cons:. It's a little slow at loading and starting Blu-Ray DVD's. Several titles simply produce a message "This disc connot be played". Risky firmware upgrades.. 
Summary:. I have two identical BD-P1600's connected to two Samsung televisions, one took the May 2010 firmware upgrade without incident, the second player locked up and became unusable after the firmware upgrade. It has since been returned to Samsung for service. The player in question is only about 7 months old.. Any device that permits firmware upgrades MUST have a hard reset. It is ludicrous that after a failed firmware upgrade one can't reset the device oneself. Instead it must be sent to an "Authorized Samsung Service" facility for repair.. 

